<p><placeName>Herculaneum </placeName><date when="1814-06-13">June 13 1814</date></p>
<p>Dear Sir</p>

<p>I am under the necessity of Addressing you Once More on the
Subject of lead&#8212;<persName>Mr Scott</persName>s boat will be here on <date when="1814-06-16">Thursday </date>and he
holdes one of my Recepts and I have not [the amt of lead to] take
it up: I wish you either to send me [enough to] <placeName>St. Geneveive</placeName> to
meete his Boat [If] you do not; I do not know what I am to do for
I can not get the lead here at this time. I hope you will consider
my Situation and send me Reliefe the Amot of the Receip is about
2300&#8212;<persName>Coll Hammonds</persName> is Just from <placeName>St Louis</placeName> he tells me that he
saw a Gentleman theire that told him that he saw <persName>Phelps </persName>at the <placeName>play
hous in new Orleans</placeName> in Company with several of the <persName>Ladyes </persName>of the
Town and that he was a dashing [mutilated] Table and with a
high [mutilated]</p>

<p><persName>Elias Bates</persName></p>
<p>The <placeName>Store </placeName>will be finished this Weeke or the begening of Next&#8212;</p>
<p>[Addressed:] <persName>Mr James Bryan</persName><placeName> Mine-[a-Burton]</placeName></p>

        </div1>
